President Obama made several phone calls to foreign leaders on February 11, 2009. He spoke to President Peres of Israel to congratulate the Israeli people on their recent elections and discuss the importance of achieving a two-state solution to the Israeli-Palestinian conflict. He also had a friendly and productive call with Italian Prime Minister Berlusconi, discussing cooperation on various issues including the global financial crisis, upcoming summits, Iran, Middle East peace efforts, and energy security. Additionally, President Obama had a productive conversation with Pakistani President Zardari, expressing support for Pakistan's democracy and commitment to a strong partnership. They agreed to work together on counter-terrorism and economic development to promote peace and prosperity in Pakistan and the region.